<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5955> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5955" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Though probably not one of the conspirators (despite Plut. Caes. 68.3; see Dio 44.50.4; Zonar. 10. 12), this brother of Caesar's first wife joined the conspirators and took off the insignia of his praetorship since they were the gift of a tyrant (Val. Max. 9.9.1; Suet. Iul. 85; Plut. Brut. 18.6-7; 20.5-6; App. BC 2.121), but when he resumed them for the Senate meeting of March 17 he required the protection of Lepidus (App. BC 2.126, cf. 137). He became such an object of hatred to the crowd at Caesar's funeral that they killed a Tribune named Cinna by mistake for him (see Tribunes of the Plebs). He sponsored the recall of Caesetius and Marullus (see Tribunes of the Plebs; Nic. Dam. Vit. Caes. 22, FGrH 2A.406) after Caesar's death, and in the Senate meeting on November 28 refused to share in the allotment of provinces (Cic. Phil. 3.25)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10469> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10469" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/32> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Joined Sertorians in 77, after Lepidan tumult, services in Spain not recorded" .
